PRETORIA - Nineteen people were injured, four critically, when a minibus taxi and a bakkie collided on the R114 on the outskirts of Centurion in Pretoria on Saturday morning. ER24 paramedics, along with other services, arrived on the scene to find the bakkie on the side of the road while the taxi had come to a stop in the middle of the road, ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said. READ: Nearly 1 million cars stopped in SA this festive season "The taxi had been completely ripped open in the collision. The occupants of the taxi were found scattered around the scene." Paramedics assessed the patients and found that two occupants of the bakkie and 17 taxi passengers had been injured. Four people from the taxi sustained critical injuries, while the remaining patients sustained minor to moderate injuries. The cause of the collision is not yet known, Meiring said. African News Agency